 schwierigen Werk.  aThis volume presents the first modern edition and German translation of De misera eruditorum (On the Misery of Scholars) by Martinus Schoockius (1614–1669), Prof. of Philosophy in Groningen and court historiographer to the Great Elector in Frankfurt/O. Schoock wrote numerous historical and philosophical treatises. This volume offers an extensive introduction to and running commentary on this difficult work.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aEdition. 4aElend. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aMiseria. 4aSchoockius.  aEarly modern period.  aSchoockius.  aedition.  amiseria.  amisery.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z97831113182640 cprintz978311120777340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311120876340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111208763423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111208763/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131826-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023